content: I've been finding a lot of old documents and papers that I don't need anymore. I'm also discovering some old photos and mementos that I had forgotten about. It's been a nice trip down memory lane, but I'm trying to stay focused on the task at hand. Speaking of which, do you have any advice on how to pack lamps and electronics? I have a few fragile lamps and some electronics with a lot of cords that I'm not sure how to pack.
